communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Rabies is not a disease to be taken lightly. It can kill people and
animals. Vaccination of animals (including horses and cattle) is for their
protection as well as that of the owners and other people. The human
population is encroaching upon the habitat of wild animals, which increases
the potential for contact with human beings. The lack of water in many
places along the eastern seaboard may well be driving animals to look for
water, and even food, in places where they may not normally be found. Bats
may be the most dangerous as they can bite without humans being aware of
it. - Mod.TG

The states discussed in this posting can be located on the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=40,-97.6,4>. - CopyEd.MJ]
